#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:452
msgid "Runtime Dispatch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:454
msgid ""
"Importing NumPy triggers a scan of the available CPU features from the set "
"of dispatchable features. You can restrict this scan by setting the "
"environment variable ``NPY_DISABLE_CPU_FEATURES`` to a comma-, tab-, or "
"space-separated list of features to disable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:459
msgid "For instance, on ``x86_64`` this will disable ``X86_V4``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:461
msgid "NPY_DISABLE_CPU_FEATURES=\"X86_V4\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:463
msgid ""
"This will raise an error if parsing fails or if the feature was not enabled "
"through the ``cpu-dispatch`` build option. If the feature is supported by "
"the build but not available on the current CPU, a warning will be emitted "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:467
msgid "Tracking Dispatched Functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:469
msgid ""
"You can discover which CPU targets are enabled for different optimized "
"functions using the Python function ``numpy.lib.introspect.opt_func_info``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:472
msgid "This function offers two optional arguments for filtering results:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:474
msgid "``func_name`` - For refining function names"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:475
msgid "``signature`` - For specifying data types in the signatures"
msgstr ""

